Cape Town - Three men and a young boy were killed when two minibus taxis and a car collided on the R61 outside of Beaufort West on Monday morning, &nbsp;paramedics said. Six others were critically injured, among them another young boy.&nbsp; The six critical patients together with 13 others, also seriously injured but in a stable condition, were rushed to Beaufort West Provincial Hospital by Western Cape Government Health Emergency Medical Services. IOL